definition.value: An alpha-amino-acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-amino-5-oxohexanoic acid.
A pyrimidine 2',3'-dideoxyribonucleoside compound having cytosine as the nucleobase.
A pyrazolo[1,5-a]pyrimidine having a nitrile group at position 3 and a 3-(N-ethylacetamido)phenyl substituent at the 7-position.
A sesquiterpene lactone that is decahydroazuleno[4,5-b]furan-2(3H)-one substituted by methylidene groups at positions 3, 6 and 9 and a hydroxy group at position 8.
